  "text": "Position of selected site: We estimated the approximate position of the putative selected site using both the composite likelihood ratio approach by [CITATION_1] and the test by [CITATION_2] . Input files were prepared with parameter settings (N e , R, u, and a) as mentioned above. The current frequency of the beneficial allele was set to 1 and, given the observed pattern of variation (see results), a very recent fixation of the beneficial allele was assumed (t ¼ 0). Two-locus sampling probability tables under the selective sweep model and the neutral model were kindly provided by Y. Kim (personal communication) and R. Hudson (http:/ / home.uchicago.edu/rhudson1/), respectively.",
